Encryption is the method to save the data in the secure format and can able to see only with decrypt key.
    Example:
      A SSN number of the person is 567-789 and it can be encrypted as $%^&*(

The types of Encryption
    IN Rest Encryption
    IN transit Encryption
    Columnar Encryption
    Full disk Encryption

IN Rest Encryption
   The data is encrypted in the disk where it is stored.The person can see the disk with the decrpty key.
IN transit Encryption
   The data is encrypted while transferring or doing transaction within the database and the user.
Columnar Encrption
    Certain columns in a database will be encrypted and all the other columns will be remain encrypted.
Full Disk Encryption
    The disk can be fully encrypted.Like hard disk is completely encrypted.

    
